Did it without making 2 different arrays, just handle the base case class Solution {    public int func(int nums[],int start,int n){        int prev = nums[start];        int prev2 = 0;        for(int i=start+1;i<n;i++){            int take = nums[i] + prev2;            int nottake = 0 + prev;            int cur = Math.max(take,nottake);            prev2 = prev;            prev = cur;        }        return prev;    }    public int rob(int[] nums) {        if(nums.length==1) return nums[0];       return Math.max(func(nums,0,nums.length-1),func(nums,1,nums.length));    }}

Code is here class Solution {public:     ///// tabulation approach     int solve(vector<int>& nums) {        int n = nums.size();        vector<int>dp(n,-1);        // base case         dp[0] = nums[0];        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){            int take = nums[i]; if(i>1) take+=dp[i-2];            int not_take = 0+dp[i-1];            dp[i] = max(take,not_take);        }        return dp[n-1];    }     int rob(vector<int>& nums) {        int ind = nums.size();int n=nums.size();        vector<int>temp1,temp2;        if(n==1) return nums[n-1];        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){            if(i!=n-1) temp1.push_back(nums[i]);            if(i!=0) temp2.push_back(nums[i]);        }        int first_half = solve(temp1);        int sec_half = solve(temp2);        return max(first_half,sec_half);    }};

JAVASCRIPT SOL:-function rob(nums) {  let n = nums.length;   if (n === 0) return 0;  //   if (n === 1) return nums[0];  if (n < 4) return Math.max(...nums);   function findMax(start, end) {    let prev = 0;    let cur = 0;     for (let i = start; i <= end; i++) {      const temp = cur;      cur = Math.max(prev + nums[i], cur);      prev = temp;    }    return cur;  }  // start from first house and leave last house  const max1 = findMax(0, n - 2);  // start from second house till end and leave first house  const max2 = findMax(1, n - 1);   return Math.max(max1, max2);} const nums = [1, 2, 3];console.log(rob(nums));

If we dont want to use up extra space for the temp arrays we can send the start and end indicesHere is my approach in c++,#include <bits/stdc++.h>long long int maxSum(vector<int> &nums, int start, int end){     int n = nums.size();    vector<long long int> dp(n - 1, 0);    dp[dp.size() - 1] = nums[end];     for (int i = dp.size() - 2; i >= 0; i--)    {        long long int notPick = dp[i + 1];        long long int pick = nums[i + start];        if (i + 2 < dp.size())        {            pick += dp[i + 2];        }        dp[i] = max(pick, notPick);    }     return dp[0];} long long int houseRobber(vector<int>& valueInHouse){    if (valueInHouse.size() == 1) return (long long int)valueInHouse[0];    return (long long int)(max(maxSum(valueInHouse, 0, valueInHouse.size() - 2), maxSum(valueInHouse, 1, valueInHouse.size() - 1)));}

C++ || Memoization || Tabulation || Space OptimizationMemoizationTC = O(2n)SC = O(3n) class Solution {    int memo(int i, int check, vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& dp) {        if(i < 0) return 0;        if(check == nums.size() - 1 && i == 0) return 0;        if(dp[i] != -1) return dp[i];        int pick = nums[i] + memo(i - 2, check, nums, dp);        int not_pick = memo(i - 1, check, nums, dp);        return dp[i] = max(pick, not_pick);    }public:    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {        int n = nums.size();        if(n == 1) return nums[0];        vector<int> dp(n, - 1);        vector<int> dp2(n, - 1);        return max(memo(n-1, n-1, nums, dp), memo(n-2, n-2, nums, dp2));    }}; TabulationTC = O(2n)SC = O(2n) class Solution {    int tab(int check, vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& dp) {        int n = check == nums.size() - 1 ? nums.size() : nums.size()-1;         for(int i = 2; i < n; i++){            int pick = nums[i] + dp[i - 2];            int not_pick = dp[i - 1];            dp[i] = max(pick, not_pick);        }           return dp[n - 1];     }public:    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {        int n = nums.size();        if(n == 1) return nums[0];        vector<int> dp(n, - 1);        vector<int> dp2(n, - 1);        dp[0] = nums[0], dp[1] = max(nums[0], nums[1]);        dp2[0] = 0, dp2[1] = nums[1];        return max(tab(n-2, nums, dp), tab(n-1, nums, dp2));    }}; Space OptimizationTC = O(2n)SC = O(1) class Solution {    int dp(int prev2, int prev, int check, vector<int>& nums) {        int n = check == nums.size() - 1 ? nums.size() : nums.size()-1;        int curr = max(nums[0], nums[1]); // for the case where nums.size() == 2;         for(int i = 2; i < n; i++){            int pick = nums[i] + prev2;            int not_pick = prev;            curr = max(pick, not_pick);            prev2 = prev;            prev = curr;        }           return curr;     }public:    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {        // space optimization        int n = nums.size();        if(n == 1) return nums[0];        return max(dp(nums[0], max(nums[0], nums[1]), n-2, nums), dp(0, nums[1], n-1, nums));    }};

BETTER SOLUTIONclass Solution {    // Memoization    public int solve(int start, int end, int[] dp, int[] arr) {        if (start > end) {            return 0;        }        if (dp[start] != -1) {            return dp[start];        }        int pick = arr[start] + solve(start + 2, end, dp, arr);        int notpick = 0+solve(start + 1, end, dp, arr);        return dp[start] = Math.max(pick, notpick);    }     public int rob(int[] nums) {        int n = nums.length;        if (n == 1) {            return nums[0];        }        int[] dp1 = new int[n];        int[] dp2 = new int[n];        Arrays.fill(dp1, -1);        Arrays.fill(dp2, -1);        int max1 = solve(0, n - 2, dp1, nums);        int max2 = solve(1, n - 1, dp2, nums);        return Math.max(max1, max2);        /* Calculate the maximum amount of money that can be robbed when excluding the first house        dp1[0] = 0;        dp1[1] = nums[1];        for (int i = 2; i < n; i++) {            dp1[i] = Math.max(dp1[i - 2] + nums[i], dp1[i - 1]);        }         // Calculate the maximum amount of money that can be robbed when excluding the last house        dp2[0] = nums[0];        dp2[1] = Math.max(nums[0], nums[1]);        for (int i = 2; i < n - 1; i++) {            dp2[i] = Math.max(dp2[i - 2] + nums[i], dp2[i - 1]);        }         // Return the maximum amount of money between the two cases        return Math.max(dp1[n - 1], dp2[n - 2]);*/    }}

class Solution {    public int rob(int[] nums) {        int n = nums.length;        if (n == 1) {            return nums[0];        }        // Variables to keep track of the maximum amount of money at each step        int prev1 = 0; // Maximum amount when excluding the first house        int prev2 = 0; // Maximum amount when excluding the last house        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {            int temp = prev1;             prev1 = Math.max(prev2 + nums[i], prev1);             prev2 = Math.max(temp, prev2);         }         int max1 = prev1;        prev1 = 0;        prev2 = 0;         for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {            int temp = prev1;            prev1 = Math.max(prev2 + nums[i], prev1);            prev2 = Math.max(temp, prev2);        }        int max2 = prev1;         return Math.max(max1, max2);    }}  @takeUforward have look on this solution

All thanks to StriverBrute Force Approach:-long long int recursive(int ind, vector<int>&a,int end){    if(ind<0 || ind==end) return 0;     if(ind==0) return a[0];     long long int pick = recursive(ind-2,a,end) + a[ind];    long long int not_pick = recursive(ind-1,a,end) + 0;    return max(pick,not_pick);}if(valueInHouse.size()==1) return valueInHouse[0];    return max(recursive(valueInHouse.size()-1,valueInHouse,0),recursive(valueInHouse.size()-2,valueInHouse,INT_MAX));------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Memoization:-long long int recursive(int ind, vector<int>&a,int end,vector<long long int>&dp){    if(ind<0 || ind==end) return 0;    if(dp[ind]!=0) return dp[ind];    if(ind==0) return a[0];     long long int pick = recursive(ind-2,a,end,dp) + a[ind];    long long int not_pick = recursive(ind-1,a,end,dp) + 0;    return dp[ind] = max(pick,not_pick);}long long int n = valueInHouse.size();    if(valueInHouse.size()==1) return valueInHouse[0];    vector<long long int>dp1(n,0);    vector<long long int>dp2(n-1,0);    return max(recursive(valueInHouse.size()-1,valueInHouse,0,dp1),recursive(valueInHouse.size()-2,valueInHouse,INT_MAX,dp2));------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Tabulation:-long long int tabu(int ind, int end,vector<int>&a){    vector<long long int>dp(end,0);    dp[ind] = a[ind];    for(int i = ind+1; i<end; i++){        long long int pick = a[i];        (i>1)? pick+=dp[i-2] : pick+=0;        long long int not_pick = dp[i-1] + 0;        dp[i] = max(pick,not_pick);    }    return dp[end-1];}if(valueInHouse.size()==1) return valueInHouse[0];    if(valueInHouse.size()==2) return max(valueInHouse[0],valueInHouse[1]);    long int n = valueInHouse.size();    return max(tabu(0,n-1,valueInHouse),tabu(1,n,valueInHouse));------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Space Optimizationlong long int space_opti(int ind, int end, vector<int>&a){    long long int prev = a[ind];    long long int prev2 = 0;    for(int i = ind+1; i<end; i++){        long long int pick = a[i];        (i>1)? pick+=prev2 : pick+=0;        long long int not_pick = prev + 0;        long long int curri = max(pick,not_pick);        prev2 = prev;        prev = curri;    }    return prev;}

C++ Code for T.C - O(2N) | S.C - O(1)-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------long long int solve(int start, int end, vector<int>& nums) {  long long int prev2 = 0, prev1 = 0;  for (long long int i = start; i <= end; i++) {    // Take = prev2 + nums[i] | notTake =  0 + prev1    long long int curr = max(prev2 + nums[i], prev1);    prev2 = prev1;    prev1 = curr;  }  return prev1;}long long int houseRobber(vector<int>& nums) {  int n = nums.size();  if (n == 0) return 0;  if (n == 1) return nums[0];  // if (n == 2) return max(nums[0], nums[1]);  long long int ans1 = solve(0, n - 2, nums);  long long int ans2 = solve(1, n - 1 , nums);  return max(ans1, ans2);}

Space optimised solution is here bounded the array size for two callslong long solve1(int j,int n,vector<int> &arr){    long long prev1 = arr[j],prev2,next;    for(int i = j+1; i < n; i++){        long long pick = arr[i];        if(i>j+1)            pick += prev2;        long long notpick = 0 + prev1;        next  = max(pick,notpick);        prev2 = prev1;        prev1 = next;    }    return prev1;}long long int houseRobber(vector<int>& arr){    int n = arr.size();    if(n == 1)return arr[0];    long long ans1 = solve1(0,n-1,arr);    long long ans2 = solve1(1,n,arr);    return max(ans1,ans2);}

/*with space optimization (no need vector temp1 and temp2)*/int robhelp(int start,int end,vector<int> &nums) {        int prev1=nums[start];        int prev2=0,curr;        int fs,ss;        if(end-start==1)            return nums[start];        for(int i=start+1;i<end;i++)        {           fs=nums[i];           if(i>start+1)             fs+=prev2;           ss=prev1;           curr=max(fs,ss);            prev2=prev1;            prev1=curr;        }        return curr;    }    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {        int n=nums.size();        if(n==1)            return nums[0];       return max(robhelp(0,n-1,nums),robhelp(1,n,nums)) ;     }

Code without using extra space .class Solution {private:    int findMax(int start,int end,vector<int>&nums){        int prev = nums[start];        int prev2 = 0 ;        for(int i=start+1;i<end;i++){             int pick = nums[i];            if(i>1)                pick += prev2;            int notPick = prev;            int curr = max(pick,notPick);            prev2 = prev;            prev = curr;        }        return prev;    }public:    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {        int n = nums.size();        if(n==1)return nums[0];        if(n==2)return max(nums[0],nums[1]);        int ans1 = findMax(0,n-1,nums);        int ans2 = findMax(1,n,nums);        return max(ans1,ans2);    }};

int pickHouse(vector<int>v,int st,int end){        int prev=v[st];        int prev2=0;        for(int i=st+1;i<=end;i++){            int pick=v[i]+prev2,notPick=prev;            prev2=prev;            prev=max(pick,notPick);        }        return prev;    }    int rob(vector<int>& nums) {        int n=nums.size();        if(n==1)return nums[0];        return max(pickHouse(nums,0,n-2),pickHouse(nums,1,n-1));    }

In the article it is mentioned that the space required is O(1) but the solution uses O(N) extra space for creating two additional arrays.Here is the true O(1) space solutionlong long int houseRobberUtil(vector<int>& valueInHouse, bool check) //check=true if we pick the first 1st element and false if we don't pick the first element.{	long long int prev1,prev2;	int i,n;	if(check)	{		prev2=valueInHouse[0];		i=1;		n=valueInHouse.size();		n-=1;	}	else	{		prev2=valueInHouse[1];		i=2;		n=valueInHouse.size();	}	prev1=prev2;	long long int ans=0;	while(i<n)	{		long long int pick=valueInHouse[i];		if(check)		{			if(i>1)				pick+=prev2;		}		else		{			if(i>2)				pick+=prev2;		}		long long int notPick=prev1;		ans=max(pick,notPick);		prev2=prev1;		prev1=ans;		i++;	}	return prev1;}long long int houseRobber(vector<int>& valueInHouse){	if(valueInHouse.size()==1)		return valueInHouse[0];	long long int inc=houseRobberUtil(valueInHouse,true);	long long int exc=houseRobberUtil(valueInHouse,false);	return max(inc,exc);}
